1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง3196, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 274, ยง1, is repealed.
3 SUMMARY
44 Public Law 2019, chapter 274 enacted the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section
55 3196, which requires the Department of Health and Human Services to provide coverage
66 to a MaineCare member for abortion services. Abortion services that are not federally
77 approved Medicaid services must be funded by the State.
8 This bill repeals Title 22, section 3196, removing the requirement that the department
9 fund abortion services for MaineCare members and removing the requirement that the State
10 pay when the abortion services are not covered by Medicaid.
